<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Gattyana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gattyana cirrhosa" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrhosa">Gattyana cirrhosa (Pallas, 1766)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. In the Mediterranean only reported from Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogdanos, Costantinos" journalOrPublisher="Thalassographica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="77 - 105" title="The macrozoobenthos of an Aegean Embayment" volume="6" year="1983">Bogdanos and Satsmadjis 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogdanos, C" journalOrPublisher="Thalassographica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="39 - 52" title="Contribution to the study of the zoobenthos and phytobenthos in Messolonghi lagoon" volume="7" year="1984">Bogdanos and Diapoulis 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="NCMR," journalOrPublisher="National Centre for Marine Research, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Επισκόπηση της βενθικής πανίδας στο Κεντρικό Αιγαίο Πέλαγος (Κυκλάδες- Σαρωνικός)." year="1989">NCMR 1989</bibRefCitation>
), Spain (
<bibRefCitation author="Desbruyeres, Daniel" journalOrPublisher="Vie et milieu" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="335 - 363" title="Bionomie benthique du plateau continental de la cote catalane Espagnole" volume="23" year="1973">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desbruyères">Desbruyeres</normalizedToken>
et al. 1973
</bibRefCitation>
) and Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Castelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Marina Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="323 - 373" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta" volume="15" year="2008">Castelli et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) otherwise known from boreal regions and cold water areas along the French and Spanish Atlantic coasts (
<bibRefCitation author="Dauvin, Jean-Claude" journalOrPublisher="Scientia Marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="259 - 267" title="Biodiversity and biogeographic relationships of the polychaete fauna in French Atlantic and Mediterranean waters" volume="70" year="2006">Dauvin et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, J" editor="al., Ramos MA et" journalOrPublisher="Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales. CSIC, Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta IV. Parapar J, Moreira J, Nunez J, Barnich R, Brito M del C, Fiee D, Capaccioni-Azzati R, El-Haddad M. Fauna Iberica" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Núñez">Nunez</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
); its presence in the Mediterranean could not yet be confirmed (
<bibRefCitation author="Barnich, R" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 167" title="The Aphroditoidea (Annelida: Polychaeta) of the Mediterranean Sea" volume="599" year="2003">Barnich and Fiege 2003</bibRefCitation>
). It is easily confused with 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Harmothoe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Harmothoe antilopes" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="antilopes">Harmothoe antilopes</taxonomicName>
McIntosh, 1876, a species with similar elytral structures but different notochaetae (
<bibRefCitation author="Barnich, Ruth" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1889 - 1938" title="Revision of the Mediterranean species of Harmothoe Kinberg, 1856 and Lagisca Malmgren, 1865 (Polychaeta: Polynoidae: Polynoinae) with descriptions of a new genus and a new species" volume="34" year="2000">Barnich and Fiege 2000a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
